<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,151,1039]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,800,824]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[323,614,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amphion">
<emphasis box="[323,614,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Sphaeropthalma amphion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were too rarely encountered to determine their habitat preference. Only one 
<taxonomicName box="[199,325,836,860]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amphion">
<emphasis box="[199,325,836,860]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">S. amphion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
male was collected in late October at a light trap. Ten 
<taxonomicName box="[943,1069,836,860]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amphion">
<emphasis box="[943,1069,836,860]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">S. amphion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males were found at the NTS in August at light traps and a mammal trap (
